{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871575908,"sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31bd4d001C6yYqtd2nOPSeA","messageID":"msg_d7a31aefd001f6fbaRQcD1rRvv","sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1a6cbb9f83a54b688b042aac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK, providing low-level HTTP communication for Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) operations with connection pooling, timeout management, and session header handling.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube Python SDK requires reliable HTTP communication with two backend services:\n12: \n13: - **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle (create/delete code interpreter sessions)\n14: - **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution, file operations, and agent invocations\n15: \n16: The HTTP layer must handle:\n17: 1. Connection pooling for efficient resource usage\n18: 2. Configurable timeouts (connect + read)\n19: 3. Authentication token injection\n20: 4. Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n21: 5. Error handling with appropriate exceptions\n22: \n23: ### Goal\n24: \n25: Implement a robust HTTP client layer that:\n26: - Provides `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager communication\n27: - Provides `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router communication\n28: - Handles connection pooling with `requests.Session` and `HTTPAdapter`\n29: - Manages timeouts consistently across all clients\n30: - Follows the SDK's HTTP contract specifications\n31: \n32: ### Value\n33: \n34: - **Reliability**: Consistent timeout and error handling\n35: - **Performance**: Connection pooling reduces latency\n36: - **Maintainability**: Centralized HTTP logic\n37: - **Developer Experience**: Clear API contracts\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Scope\n42: \n43: ### In-Scope\n44: \n45: | Component | Path | Description |\n46: |-----------|------|-------------|\n47: | ControlPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Workload Manager HTTP client |\n48: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Router CI operations |\n49: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Router agent invocation |\n50: | create_session | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Session with pooling |\n51: | read_token_from_file | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token file reading |\n52: | Exception classes | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Error types |\n53: \n54: ### Out-of-Scope\n55: \n56: - High-level client implementations (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n57: - Async HTTP support\n58: - Retry logic / circuit breaker\n59: - Authentication beyond token file\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n68: |------------|---------|--------|\n69: | `requests` | HTTP client | Required |\n70: | `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required |\n71: | `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required |\n72: \n73: ### Upstream\n74: \n75: - `python-sdk/design.md` — HTTP client specifications\n76: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — HTTP contract requirements\n77: \n78: ### Downstream Consumers\n79: \n80: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient** — Uses ControlPlaneClient and CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n81: 2. **AgentRuntimeClient** — Uses AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n82: 3. **SDK users** — Indirect consumers through high-level clients\n83: \n84: ### Risks\n85: \n86: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n87: |------|----------|------------|\n88: | Workload Manager unavailable | Medium | Timeout handling, clear error messages |\n89: | Token file missing | Low | Empty token (anonymous), warning log |\n90: | Connection pool exhaustion | Medium | Configurable pool size |\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## Alternatives Considered\n95: \n96: ### Option 1: httpx for async support (Not Selected)\n97: \n98: **Pros**: Native async/await, sync/async unified API\n99: **Cons**: Adds new dependency; sync `requests` sufficient for current needs\n100: \n101: ### Option 2: urllib3 directly (Not Selected)\n102: \n103: **Pros**: Lower-level control\n104: **Cons**: More boilerplate; `requests` provides better abstraction\n105: \n106: ### Option 3: aiohttp (Not Selected)\n107: \n108: **Pros**: Async-first design\n109: **Cons**: Async not in scope; different API paradigm\n110: \n111: ### Option 4: requests with HTTPAdapter (Selected)\n112: \n113: **Pros**: Existing dependency, connection pooling, familiar API, timeout handling\n114: **Cons**: Sync-only\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Technical Design\n119: \n120: ### HTTP Session Creation\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: def create_session(\n124:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n125:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n126: ) -> requests.Session:\n127:     \"\"\"Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n128: ```\n129: \n130: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n131: \n132: ### ControlPlaneClient\n133: \n134: ```python\n135: class ControlPlaneClient:\n136:     def __init__(\n137:         self,\n138:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n139:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n140:         timeout: int = 120,\n141:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n142:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n143:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n144:     ): ...\n145: \n146:     def create_session(\n147:         self,\n148:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n149:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n150:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n151:         ttl: int = 3600,\n152:     ) -> str: ...\n153: \n154:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n155: \n156:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n157: ```\n158: \n159: #### Control Plane HTTP Contract\n160: \n161: | Method | Path | Notes |\n162: |--------|------|-------|\n163: | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n164: | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success |\n165: \n166: **Headers:**\n167: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n168: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n169: \n170: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n171: \n172: **URL Resolution:**\n173: - `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n174: \n175: **Token Resolution:**\n176: - `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n177: \n178: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n179: \n180: ```python\n181: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n182:     def __init__(\n183:         self,\n184:         session_id: str,\n185:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n186:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n187:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n188:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n189:         timeout: int = 120,\n190:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n191:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n192:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n193:     ): ...\n194: \n195:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n196: \n197:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n198:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n199:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n200:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n201:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n202:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n203:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n204: ```\n205: \n206: #### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) HTTP Contract\n207: \n208: **Base URL:**\n209: - If `base_url` provided: use directly\n210: - Otherwise: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/`\n211: \n212: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n213: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n214: | POST | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n215: | POST | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n216: | POST | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n217: | GET | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n218: | GET | `api/files` | query `path` |\n219: \n220: **Headers:**\n221: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n222: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json`\n223: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only\n224: \n225: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n226: \n227: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n228: \n229: ```python\n230: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n231:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n232: \n233:     def __init__(\n234:         self,\n235:         router_url: str,\n236:         namespace: str,\n237:         agent_name: str,\n238:         timeout: int = 120,\n239:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n240:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n241:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n242:     ): ...\n243: \n244:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n245: \n246:     def invoke(\n247:         self,\n248:         session_id: str,\n249:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n250:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n251:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n252: \n253:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n254: ```\n255: \n256: #### Data Plane (Agent Runtime) HTTP Contract\n257: \n258: **Base URL:**\n259: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n260: \n261: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n262: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n263: | GET | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n264: | POST | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n265: \n266: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is method argument or `self.timeout`.\n267: \n268: ### Token File Reading\n269: \n270: ```python\n271: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n272:     \"\"\"Read token from file, return stripped contents or empty string on error.\"\"\"\n273: ```\n274: \n275: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n276: \n277: ### Exception Hierarchy\n278: \n279: ```python\n280: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n281:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n282:     pass\n283: \n284: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n285:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n286:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n287:         self.stderr = stderr\n288:         self.command = command\n289:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n290: \n291: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n292:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n293:     pass\n294: \n295: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n296:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n297:     pass\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## Implementation Plan\n303: \n304: ### Phase 1: Core HTTP Utilities\n305: \n306: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/http.py` — `create_session()` with HTTPAdapter\n307: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py` — `read_token_from_file()`\n308: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/log.py` — `get_logger()`\n309: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` — empty module marker\n310: \n311: ### Phase 2: Exception Classes\n312: \n313: - [ ] Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` — exception hierarchy\n314: - [ ] Define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n315: \n316: ### Phase 3: ControlPlaneClient\n317: \n318: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n319: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n320: - [ ] Implement `create_session()` — POST to Workload Manager\n321: - [ ] Implement `delete_session()` — DELETE with 404-as-success handling\n322: - [ ] Implement token resolution (arg/env/file)\n323: - [ ] Add timeout handling\n324: \n325: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n326: \n327: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n328: - [ ] Implement base URL construction\n329: - [ ] Implement `_request()` — low-level HTTP\n330: - [ ] Implement `execute_command()` — POST to api/execute\n331: - [ ] Implement `write_file()` — base64 upload\n332: - [ ] Implement `upload_file()` — multipart upload\n333: - [ ] Implement `download_file()` — streaming download\n334: - [ ] Implement `list_files()` — GET with query\n335: - [ ] Add session header management\n336: \n337: ### Phase 5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n338: \n339: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n340: - [ ] Implement base URL construction\n341: - [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET + header extraction\n342: - [ ] Implement `invoke()` — POST JSON with session header\n343: - [ ] Add timeout handling\n344: \n345: ### Phase 6: Integration & Exports\n346: \n347: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` exports\n348: - [ ] Verify all clients work together\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Acceptance Criteria\n353: \n354: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n355: |----|----------|-----------------|\n356: | HTTP-001 | create_session with pooling | Session has HTTPAdapter mounted |\n357: | HTTP-002 | ControlPlaneClient create_session | POST with correct JSON body, returns sessionId |\n358: | HTTP-003 | ControlPlaneClient delete_session (404) | Returns True |\n359: | HTTP-004 | ControlPlaneClient token from file | Reads from default Kubernetes path |\n360: | HTTP-005 | DataPlaneClient execute_command | POST with correct JSON, timeout handling |\n361: | HTTP-006 | DataPlaneClient write_file | POST with base64 content |\n362: | HTTP-007 | DataPlaneClient upload_file | Multipart POST with session header |\n363: | HTTP-008 | DataPlaneClient download_file | Streaming GET |\n364: | HTTP-009 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap | GET extracts x-agentcube-session-id |\n365: | HTTP-010 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke | POST with correct headers |\n366: | HTTP-011 | Timeout tuple format | (connect_timeout, read_timeout) |\n367: | HTTP-012 | Session header case | Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Timeline Estimate\n372: \n373: | Phase | Effort |\n374: |-------|--------|\n375: | Core HTTP Utilities | 1 hour |\n376: | Exception Classes | 0.5 hours |\n377: | ControlPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n378: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 2.5 hours |\n379: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n380: | Integration & Tests | 2 hours |\n381: | **Total** | **9 hours** |\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Relationship to AR-027 / AR-028\n386: \n387: AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) and AR-028 (SDK AgentRuntimeClient) are high-level clients that consume this HTTP layer.\n388: \n389: AR-029 provides the foundation:\n390: - Connection pooling\n391: - Timeout management\n392: - HTTP contracts\n393: - Session header handling\n394: - Error types\n395: \n396: The high-level clients delegate HTTP operations to these low-level clients, providing developer-friendly APIs on top.\n\n(End of file - total 396 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK, providing low-level HTTP communication for Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) operations with connection pooling, timeout management, and session header handling.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires reliable HTTP communication with two backend services:\n\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle (create/delete code interpreter sessions)\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution, file operations, and agent invocations\n\nThe HTTP layer must handle:\n1. Connection pooling for efficient resource usage\n2. Configurable timeouts (connect + read)\n3. Authentication token injection\n4. Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871575879,"end":1775871575907}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871575910,"sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31c1c9001uFg42JtgWN02nU","messageID":"msg_d7a31aefd001f6fbaRQcD1rRvv","sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a789313355474ca884150d70","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775871575882,"end":1775871575909}}}}
