{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871585184,"sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a31e75b001sdGF7k3bwqvxS1","messageID":"msg_d7a31dbe9001ID5ZsbOEKJxiKA","sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_29a3224de92f4fdb9b04032a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-030\n4: - **Module**: manifests\n5: - **Language**: YAML\n6: - **Size**: L\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: - **Stage**: ST-1\n9: \n10: ## 1. Architecture\n11: \n12: ### 1.1 Overview\n13: \n14: The AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\n15: \n16: ### 1.2 Chart Structure\n17: \n18: ```\n19: manifests/charts/base/\n20: ├── Chart.yaml\n21: ├── values.yaml\n22: ├── crds/\n23: │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n24: │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n25: └── templates/\n26:     ├── _helpers.tpl\n27:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n28:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n29:     ├── rbac/\n30:     │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n31:     │   └── router.yaml\n32:     └── volcano/\n33:         └── agent-scheduler.yaml\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### 1.3 Components\n37: \n38: | Component | Kind | Required | Description |\n39: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n40: | Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\n41: | Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing layer |\n42: | WorkloadManager RBAC | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding | Yes | Cluster-wide permissions |\n43: | Router RBAC | ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding | Optional | Namespace-scoped permissions |\n44: | Volcano Scheduler | Multiple (SA, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) | Optional | Custom scheduler |\n45: | CRDs | CustomResourceDefinition | Yes | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n46: \n47: ## 2. Data Structures\n48: \n49: ### 2.1 Chart.yaml\n50: \n51: ```yaml\n52: apiVersion: v2\n53: name: agentcube\n54: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n55: type: application\n56: version: 0.1.0\n57: appVersion: 1.0.0\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ### 2.2 values.yaml Schema\n61: \n62: | Path | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n63: |------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n64: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` | No | Image pull secrets |\n65: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override chart name |\n66: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` | No | Override full name |\n67: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` | Yes | Redis address (host:port) |\n68: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` | No | Redis password |\n69: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Router replica count |\n70: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` | No | Router image |\n71: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n72: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n73: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n74: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n75: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` | No | Container port |\n76: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n77: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n78: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n79: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n80: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n81: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` | No | Service account name |\n82: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` | No | Create RBAC |\n83: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Replica count |\n84: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` | No | Image repository |\n85: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n86: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n87: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` | No | Service type |\n88: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` | No | Service port |\n89: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` | No | CPU limit |\n90: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` | No | Memory limit |\n91: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` | No | CPU request |\n92: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` | No | Memory request |\n93: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` | No | Additional env vars |\n94: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` | No | Enable scheduler |\n95: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` | No | Scheduler replicas |\n96: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` | No | Scheduler image |\n97: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` | No | Image pull policy |\n98: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` | No | Image tag |\n99: \n100: ## 3. API Contracts\n101: \n102: ### 3.1 Workload Manager Service\n103: \n104: ```yaml\n105: apiVersion: v1\n106: kind: Service\n107: metadata:\n108:   name: workloadmanager\n109:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n110: spec:\n111:   type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}\n112:   selector:\n113:     app: workloadmanager\n114:   ports:\n115:     - port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n116:       targetPort: http\n117:       protocol: TCP\n118:       name: http\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### 3.2 Workload Manager Deployment\n122: \n123: | Field | Source | Description |\n124: |-------|--------|-------------|\n125: | `replicas` | `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas` | Replica count |\n126: | `serviceAccountName` | `\"workloadmanager\"` | Fixed SA |\n127: | `image` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.workloadmanager.image.tag` | Container image |\n128: | `imagePullPolicy` | `.Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | Pull policy |\n129: | `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n130: | `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n131: | `env.AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `.Release.Namespace` | Release namespace |\n132: | `livenessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n133: | `readinessProbe` | `/health` | Health endpoint |\n134: | `resources` | `.Values.workloadmanager.resources` | Resource limits |\n135: \n136: ### 3.3 Router Service\n137: \n138: ```yaml\n139: apiVersion: v1\n140: kind: Service\n141: metadata:\n142:   name: agentcube-router\n143:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n144: spec:\n145:   type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}\n146:   selector:\n147:     app: agentcube-router\n148:   ports:\n149:     - port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n150:       targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n151:       protocol: TCP\n152:       name: http\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### 3.4 Router Deployment\n156: \n157: | Field | Source | Description |\n158: |-------|--------|-------------|\n159: | `replicas` | `.Values.router.replicas` | Replica count |\n160: | `serviceAccountName` | `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` or `\"agentcube-router\"` | Conditional SA |\n161: | `image` | `.Values.router.image.repository` + `:` + `.Values.router.image.tag` | Container image |\n162: | `env.WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` | Internal URL |\n163: | `env.REDIS_ADDR` | `.Values.redis.addr` | Redis address |\n164: | `env.REDIS_PASSWORD` | `.Values.redis.password` | Redis password |\n165: | `args` | `--debug` if `.Values.router.debug` | Debug flag |\n166: | `livenessProbe` | `/health/live` | Health endpoint |\n167: | `readinessProbe` | `/health/ready` | Health endpoint |\n168: \n169: ### 3.5 Workload Manager RBAC\n170: \n171: ```yaml\n172: apiVersion: v1\n173: kind: ServiceAccount\n174: metadata:\n175:   name: workloadmanager\n176:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n177: ---\n178: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n179: kind: ClusterRole\n180: metadata:\n181:   name: workloadmanager\n182: rules:\n183:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n184:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n185:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n186:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n187:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n188:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n189:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n190:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n191:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n192:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n193:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\", \"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n194:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"update\"]\n195:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n196:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n197:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n198:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n199:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n200:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n201:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n202:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n203:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n204:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n205:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n206:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n207: ---\n208: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n209: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n210: metadata:\n211:   name: workloadmanager\n212: subjects:\n213:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n214:     name: workloadmanager\n215:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n216: roleRef:\n217:   kind: ClusterRole\n218:   name: workloadmanager\n219:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ### 3.6 Router RBAC (Optional)\n223: \n224: Rendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n225: \n226: ```yaml\n227: apiVersion: v1\n228: kind: ServiceAccount\n229: metadata:\n230:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n231:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n232: ---\n233: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n234: kind: Role\n235: metadata:\n236:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n237:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n238: rules:\n239:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n240:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n241:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n242: ---\n243: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n244: kind: RoleBinding\n245: metadata:\n246:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n247:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n248: subjects:\n249:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n250:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n251:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n252: roleRef:\n253:   kind: Role\n254:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n255:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### 3.7 Volcano Scheduler (Optional)\n259: \n260: Rendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n261: \n262: | Resource | Name | Description |\n263: |----------|------|-------------|\n264: | ServiceAccount | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Scheduler SA |\n265: | ConfigMap | `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` | Scheduler config |\n266: | ClusterRole | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Full scheduling permissions |\n267: | ClusterRoleBinding | `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` | RBAC binding |\n268: | Service | `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` | Scheduler service |\n269: | Deployment | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Scheduler deployment |\n270: \n271: ## 4. Error Handling\n272: \n273: ### 4.1 Validation Errors\n274: \n275: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n276: |----------|-----------|--------|\n277: | AR-030-001-A | Chart.yaml missing/invalid | `helm lint` fails |\n278: | AR-030-001-B | values.yaml missing keys | Template render failure |\n279: | AR-030-010-A | `helm lint` fails | Exit code != 0 |\n280: | AR-030-010-B | Template render error | Helm error message |\n281: \n282: ### 4.2 Runtime Errors\n283: \n284: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n285: |----------|-----------|--------|\n286: | redis.addr not set | Empty string | Deployment pods will fail |\n287: | Invalid namespace | Special characters | Helm error |\n288: | RBAC conflict | Existing role with same name | Helm upgrade fails |\n289: \n290: ### 4.3 Conditional Rendering Errors\n291: \n292: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n293: |----------|-----------|--------|\n294: | router.rbac.create invalid | Non-boolean | Template type error |\n295: | volcano.scheduler.enabled invalid | Non-boolean | Template type error |\n296: \n297: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n298: \n299: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n300: \n301: | Test | Method | Expected Result |\n302: |------|--------|-----------------|\n303: | Chart.yaml structure | `helm lint` | Pass with exit code 0 |\n304: | values.yaml schema | YAML parsing | All keys present |\n305: | Template syntax | `helm template` | Valid YAML output |\n306: | Conditional rendering | Override values | Correct resources rendered |\n307: \n308: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n309: \n310: | Test | Environment | Validation |\n311: |------|-------------|------------|\n312: | Helm install | kind cluster | Namespace created, all resources deployed |\n313: | Helm upgrade | Running cluster | No disruption, resources updated |\n314: | Optional RBAC | `router.rbac.create: true` | Role/RoleBinding created |\n315: | Optional Volcano | `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true` | Scheduler pods running |\n316: | Redis env vars | Custom values | Pods have correct env |\n317: \n318: ### 5.3 Test Commands\n319: \n320: ```bash\n321: # Lint check\n322: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n323: \n324: # Template rendering\n325: helm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n326:   --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n327:   --set redis.password=secret\n328: \n329: # Install (requires cluster)\n330: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n331:   --namespace agentcube \\\n332:   --create-namespace \\\n333:   --set redis.addr=redis:6379\n334: \n335: # Full render with all options\n336: helm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n337:   --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n338:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n339:   --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n343: \n344: | ID | Criterion | Verification |\n345: |----|-----------|--------------|\n346: | AC030-001 | Chart.yaml with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 | `helm lint` |\n347: | AC030-002 | values.yaml contains all documented keys | YAML parsing |\n348: | AC030-003 | Helm install creates namespace | `kubectl get ns` |\n349: | AC030-004 | Workload Manager REDIS_ADDR env | Pod inspection |\n350: | AC030-005 | Router REDIS_ADDR env | Pod inspection |\n351: | AC030-006 | Workload Manager replicas configurable | Template inspection |\n352: | AC030-007 | Router WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL set | Pod env inspection |\n353: | AC030-008 | ClusterRole contains required rules | YAML inspection |\n354: | AC030-009 | Router RBAC conditional rendering | Template render |\n355: | AC030-010 | Volcano scheduler conditional | Template render |\n356: | AC030-011 | CRDs in crds/ directory | Directory listing |\n357: | AC030-012 | Helm template renders without error | Exit code 0 |\n358: | AC030-013 | Helm lint passes | Exit code 0 |\n359: \n360: ## 7. Dependencies\n361: \n362: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n363: |------------|---------|---------|\n364: | Helm | 3.x | Chart rendering and installation |\n365: | Kubernetes | 1.19+ | API versions used |\n366: | controller-gen | v0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n367: \n368: ## 8. Non-Requirements\n369: \n370: The following are explicitly out of scope:\n371: \n372: - Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n373: - Ingress configuration\n374: - Prometheus/Grafana monitoring\n375: - Redis deployment (external)\n376: - Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n377: - Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n378: - Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n379: - Custom Ingress or NetworkPolicy configurations\n\n(End of file - total 379 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-030\n- **Module**: manifests\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n- **Stage**: ST-1\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\n\n### 1.2 Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775871585174,"end":1775871585181}}}}
