{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775871591474,"sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32042f001e3845zJJ4HYfRZ","messageID":"msg_d7a31ebce00178Z7FfDZxjBKTl","sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871596545,"sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a32121c001WSM5birr92AuFP","messageID":"msg_d7a31ebce00178Z7FfDZxjBKTl","sessionID":"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_abdbae64bdcb4f4188ad2612","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-030\n10: - **Module**: `manifests`\n11: - **Language**: YAML\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: - **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: AgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Requirements\n24: \n25: ### AR-030-001: Chart 结构与元数据\n26: \n27: The Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-A — Chart.yaml 包含正确的元数据\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\n32: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL pass without errors\n34: - **AND** the chart SHALL have `name: agentcube` and `version: 0.1.0` in Chart.yaml\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-B — values.yaml 包含所有必需配置项\n37: \n38: - **GIVEN** the `values.yaml` file exists in the chart\n39: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL contain keys for `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `workloadmanager.*`, `router.*`, and `volcano.scheduler.*`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-C — 目录结构完整\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the chart directory structure exists\n45: - **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL contain: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/`, and `crds/`\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### AR-030-002: Helm 安装与 Namespace 管理\n51: \n52: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation.\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-A — Helm install 创建 namespace\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n57: - **AND** `redis.addr` is set to a valid Redis address in values\n58: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace` is executed\n59: - **THEN** the namespace `agentcube` SHALL be created\n60: - **AND** all resources SHALL be deployed to that namespace\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-B — Helm upgrade 成功渲染模板\n63: \n64: - **GIVEN** the chart is already installed\n65: - **AND** values are provided with required `redis.addr`\n66: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube` runs\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL succeed without manual editing of rendered YAML\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### AR-030-003: Redis 环境变量注入\n72: \n73: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-A — Workload Manager 接收 Redis 配置\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` and `redis.password: secret123` are set in values\n78: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod starts\n79: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n80: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD=secret123` environment variable\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-B — Router 接收 Redis 配置\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` is set in values\n85: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n86: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n87: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values (empty string if not set)\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-C — Redis 密码可为空\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is set and `redis.password` is omitted or empty\n92: - **WHEN** pods start\n93: - **THEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` SHALL be set to empty string `\"\"`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ### AR-030-004: Workload Manager Deployment 配置\n98: \n99: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with configurable replica count, image, service type, resources, health probes, and environment variables.\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 409. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-030\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871596533,"end":1775871596542}}}}
