] **T074** Verify RBAC template renders correctly\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Phase 7: Router RBAC (Optional)\n+\n+- [ ] **T080** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/router.yaml`\n+- [ ] **T081** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n+- [ ] **T082** Create router ServiceAccount (with default name)\n+- [ ] **T083** Create router Role with secret permissions\n+- [ ] **T084** Create router RoleBinding\n+- [ ] **T085** Verify RBAC is NOT rendered when `router.rbac.create: false`\n+- [ ] **T086** Verify RBAC IS rendered when `router.rbac.create: true`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Phase 8: Volcano Scheduler (Optional)\n+\n+- [ ] **T090** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/agent-scheduler.yaml`\n+- [ ] **T091** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n+- [ ] **T092** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ServiceAccount\n+- [ ] **T093** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ConfigMap\n+- [ ] **T094** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRole\n+- [ ] **T095** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n+- [ ] **T096** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Service\n+- [ ] **T097** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Deployment with configurable replicas/image\n+- [ ] **T098** Verify Volcano resources are NOT rendered when disabled\n+- [ ] **T099** Verify Volcano resources ARE rendered when enabled\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Phase 9: Validation & Testing\n+\n+- [ ] **T100** Run `helm lint manifests/charts/base` - must pass\n+- [ ] **T101** Run `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379` - must succeed\n+- [ ] **T102** Verify Workload Manager Service in rendered output\n+- [ ] **T103** Verify Router Service in rendered output\n+- [ ] **T104** Verify ClusterRole with correct rules in output\n+- [ ] **T105** Verify conditional Router RBAC renders correctly (rbac.create=true)\n+- [ ] **T106** Verify conditional Volcano renders correctly (scheduler.enabled=true)\n+- [ ] **T107** Run full render with all options and verify no errors\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Phase 10: Documentation & Cleanup\n+\n+- [ ] **T110** Add README.md to chart with basic usage instructions\n+- [ ] **T111** Verify all file permissions are correct (644)\n+- [ ] **T112** Ensure no hardcoded values (all from values.yaml or helpers)\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Dependencies\n+\n+```\n+T001 → T002 → T003 → T004 → T005 → T006\n+T010 → T013 (depends on T002)\n+T020, T021 (can parallel)\n+T030-T039 (Workload Manager - sequential within phase)\n+T050-T062 (Router - sequential within phase)\n+T070-T074 (RBAC - sequential)\n+T080-T086 (Router RBAC - depends on T070-T074)\n+T090-T099 (Volcano - can parallel after T091)\n+T100-T107 (Testing - depends on all templates)\n+T110-T112 (Doc - can parallel after T100)\n+```\n+\n+**Parallel:** Phase 3 (CRDs) can be done in parallel with Phase 4-5 (Workload Manager & Router)\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- [ ] Chart.yaml with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 passes `helm lint`\n+- [ ] values.yaml contains all documented keys (redis, workloadmanager, router, volcano)\n+- [ ] Helm template renders without error: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379`\n+- [ ] Workload Manager Deployment and Service rendered\n+- [ ] Router Deployment and Service rendered\n+- [ ] Workload Manager ClusterRole with required rules\n+- [ ] Router RBAC conditional (create=false: not rendered, create=true: rendered)\n+- [ ] Volcano scheduler conditional (enabled=false: not rendered, enabled=true: rendered)\n+- [ ] CRDs present in crds/ directory\n+- [ ] All environment variables (REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE) in templates\n+\n+## Verification Commands\n+\n+```bash\n+# Lint check\n+helm lint manifests/charts/base\n+\n+# Basic template render\n+helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379\n+\n+# Full render with optional components\n+helm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n+  --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n+  --set redis.password=secret \\\n+  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n+  --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true\n+```\n+\n **Module:** pkg/apis  \n **Language:** Go  \n **Size:** S  \n **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md","before":"# AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] **T1** Define `CodeInterpreter` CRD type struct with embedded TypeMeta and ObjectMeta  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Verify: Type struct includes `Spec` and `Status` fields with appropriate JSON tags\n\n- [ ] **T2** Add kubebuilder markers for CodeInterpreter  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Markers: `+genclient`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci`  \n  - Verify: Markers present above type definition\n\n- [ ] **T3** Define `CodeInterpreterList` list type  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Verify: List type embeds TypeMeta, ListMeta and contains `Items []CodeInterpreter`\n\n- [ ] **T4** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` spec struct  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Fields: AuthMode, MaxSessionDuration, SessionTimeout, Ports, Template, WarmPoolSize  \n  - Verify: All fields with appropriate kubebuilder validation markers\n\n- [ ] **T5** Define `CodeInterpreterStatus` status struct  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Fields: Conditions, ObservedGeneration, Ready  \n  - Verify: Status struct follows standard Kubernetes status pattern\n\n- [ ] **T6** Define `AuthMode` enum type and constants  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Constants: `AuthModePicod = \"picod\"`, `AuthModeNone = \"none\"`  \n  - Verify: Enum with +kubebuilder:validation:Enum marker\n\n- [ ] **T7** Define `ContainerTemplateSp