mplates/agentcube-router.yaml` Service\n- [ ] **T051** Configure Router Service type from values (default ClusterIP)\n- [ ] **T052** Configure Router Service port and targetPort from values\n- [ ] **T053** Create Router Deployment with replicas from values\n- [ ] **T054** Configure Router image from values\n- [ ] **T055** Add WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var (internal DNS)\n- [ ] **T056** Add REDIS_ADDR env var from values\n- [ ] **T057** Add REDIS_PASSWORD env var from values\n- [ ] **T058** Add --debug arg when `.Values.router.debug` is true\n- [ ] **T059** Configure livenessProbe GET /health/live\n- [ ] **T060** Configure readinessProbe GET /health/ready\n- [ ] **T061** Configure Router resources from values\n- [ ] **T062** Add Router extraEnv support\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Workload Manager RBAC\n\n- [ ] **T070** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n- [ ] **T071** Create workloadmanager ServiceAccount\n- [ ] **T072** Create workloadmanager ClusterRole with all required rules (agents.x-k8s.io, extensions.agents.x-k8s.io, runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, core pods/secrets, tokenreviews)\n- [ ] **T073** Create workloadmanager ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] **T074** Verify RBAC template renders correctly\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Router RBAC (Optional)\n\n- [ ] **T080** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/router.yaml`\n- [ ] **T081** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n- [ ] **T082** Create router ServiceAccount (with default name)\n- [ ] **T083** Create router Role with secret permissions\n- [ ] **T084** Create router RoleBinding\n- [ ] **T085** Verify RBAC is NOT rendered when `router.rbac.create: false`\n- [ ] **T086** Verify RBAC IS rendered when `router.rbac.create: true`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Volcano Scheduler (Optional)\n\n- [ ] **T090** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/agent-scheduler.yaml`\n- [ ] **T091** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n- [ ] **T092** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ServiceAccount\n- [ ] **T093** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ConfigMap\n- [ ] **T094** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRole\n- [ ] **T095** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] **T096** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Service\n- [ ] **T097** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Deployment with configurable replicas/image\n- [ ] **T098** Verify Volcano resources are NOT rendered when disabled\n- [ ] **T099** Verify Volcano resources ARE rendered when enabled\n\n---\n\n## Phase 9: Validation & Testing\n\n- [ ] **T100** Run `helm lint manifests/charts/base` - must pass\n- [ ] **T101** Run `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379` - must succeed\n- [ ] **T102** Verify Workload Manager Service in rendered output\n- [ ] **T103** Verify Router Service in rendered output\n- [ ] **T104** Verify ClusterRole with correct rules in output\n- [ ] **T105** Verify conditional Router RBAC renders correctly (rbac.create=true)\n- [ ] **T106** Verify conditional Volcano renders correctly (scheduler.enabled=true)\n- [ ] **T107** Run full render with all options and verify no errors\n\n---\n\n## Phase 10: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T110** Add README.md to chart with basic usage instructions\n- [ ] **T111** Verify all file permissions are correct (644)\n- [ ] **T112** Ensure no hardcoded values (all from values.yaml or helpers)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\nT001 → T002 → T003 → T004 → T005 → T006\nT010 → T013 (depends on T002)\nT020, T021 (can parallel)\nT030-T039 (Workload Manager - sequential within phase)\nT050-T062 (Router - sequential within phase)\nT070-T074 (RBAC - sequential)\nT080-T086 (Router RBAC - depends on T070-T074)\nT090-T099 (Volcano - can parallel after T091)\nT100-T107 (Testing - depends on all templates)\nT110-T112 (Doc - can parallel after T100)\n```\n\n**Parallel:** Phase 3 (CRDs) can be done in parallel with Phase 4-5 (Workload Manager & Router)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Chart.yaml with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 passes `helm lint`\n- [ ] values.yaml contains all documented keys (redis, workloadmanager, router, volcano)\n- [ ] Helm template renders without error: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379`\n- [ ] Workload Manager Deployment and Service rendered\n- [ ] Router Deployment and Service rendered\n- [ ] Workload Manager ClusterRole with required rules\n- [ ] Router RBAC conditional (create=false: not rendered, create=true: rendered)\n- [ ] Volcano scheduler conditional (enabled=false: not rendered, enabled=true: rendered)\n- [ ] CRDs present in crds/ directory\n- [ ] All environment variables (REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE) in templates\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Lint check\nhelm lint manifests/charts/base\n\n# Basic template render\nhelm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379\n\n# Full render with optional components\nhelm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n  --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n  --set redis.password=secret \\\n  --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n  --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true\n```\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] **T1** Define `CodeInterpreter` CRD type struct with embedded TypeMeta and ObjectMeta  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Verify: Type struct includes `Spec` and `Status` fields with appropriate JSON tags\n\n- [ ] **T2** Add kubebuilder markers for CodeInterpreter  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Markers: `+genclient`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci`  \n  - Verify: Markers present above type definition\n\n- [ ] **T3** Define `CodeInterpreterList` list type  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Verify: List type embeds TypeMeta, ListMeta and contains `Items []CodeInterpreter`\n\n- [ ] **T4** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` spec struct  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Fields: AuthMode, MaxSessionDuration, SessionTimeout, Ports, Template, WarmPoolSize  \n  - Verify: All fields with appropriate kubebuilder validation markers\n\n- [ ] **T5** Define `CodeInterpreterStatus` status struct  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Fields: Conditions, ObservedGeneration, Ready  \n  - Verify: Status struct follows standard Kubernetes status pattern\n\n- [ ] **T6** Define `AuthMode` enum type and constants  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Constants: `AuthModePicod = \"picod\"`, `AuthModeNone = \"none\"`  \n  - Verify: Enum with +kubebuilder:validation:Enum marker\n\n- [ ] **T7** Define `ContainerTemplateSpec` supporting type  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n  - Fields: Image, Command, Args, Env, Resources, RuntimeClassName  \n  - Verify: Required Image field with proper markers\n\n- [ ] **T8** Add CodeInterpreter types to register.go  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`  \n  - Add `&CodeInterpreter{}` and `&CodeInterpreterList{}` to AddKnownTypes  \n  - Verify: Both types registered in scheme\n\n- [ ] **T9** Generate DeepCopy methods  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`  \n  - Use: `controller-gen object paths=./pkg/apis/...`  \n  - Verify: DeepCopyInto and DeepCopy methods generated for all types\n\n- [ ] **T10** Write unit tests for CodeInterpreter types  \n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`  \n  - Coverage: Type instantiation, DeepCopy, defaults validation  \n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` passes\n\n- [ ] **T11** Verify types compile correctly  \n  - Command: `go build ./pkg/apis/...`  \n  - Verify: No compilation errors\n\n- [ ] **T12** Run linter on API types  \n  - Command: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/apis/...` or `go vet ./pkg/apis/...`  \n  - Verify: No linting errors\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\nT1 → T2 → T3 → T4 → T5 → T6 → T7 → T8 → T9 → T10 → T11 → T12\n```\n\n**Parallel:** T6, T7 can be done in parallel with T4, T5\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD type defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter includes spec: authMode, maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, ports, template, warmPoolSize\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter includes status: conditions, observedGeneration, ready\n- [ ] All types implement `runtime.Object` interface\n- [ ] DeepCopy methods generated and compile correctly\n- [ ] `go build ./pkg/apis/...` passes\n- [ ] `go vet ./pkg/apis/...` passes\n- [ ] Unit tests pass\n\n---\n\n# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] **T1** 定义 `TargetPort` 共享结构体（端口配置）\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 字段: Port, Protocol, Name, PathPrefix\n  - 验证: 类型定义正确，JSON tag 完整\n\n- [ ] **T2** 定义 `PodTemplateSpec` 共享结构体（Pod 模板）\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 验证: 嵌入 metav1.ObjectMeta，可选 Spec 引用 PodSpec\n\n- [ ] **T3** 定义 `PodSpec` 共享结构体（Pod 规范子集）\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 字段: Containers, Volumes, RestartPolicy, ServiceAccountName, NodeSelector, Affinity, Tolerations 等\n  - 验证: 所有字段正确从 corev1.PodSpec 引用\n\n- [ ] **T4** 定义 `ContainerSpec` 共享结构体（容器规范子集）\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 字段: Name, Image, Command, Args, Env, Resources, Ports 等\n  - 验证: 包含容器核心字段\n\n- [ ] **T5** 定义 `AuthMode` 类型及常量\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 常量: `AuthModePicod = \"picod\"`, `AuthModeNone = \"none\"`\n  - 验证: 类型定义和常量值正确\n\n- [ ] **T6** 为 TargetPort 添加 kubebuilder 验证标记\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 验证: Port 范围 1-65535, Protocol 枚举 HTTP/HTTPS\n\n- [ ] **T7** 为 PodSpec 字段添加可选标记\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 验证: 所有字段标记 +optional\n\n- [ ] **T8** 为 ContainerSpec 字段添加验证标记\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - 验证: Name 和 Image 标记为 required\n\n- [ ] **T9** 运行 deep copy 生成\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n  - 命令: `controller-gen object paths=./pkg/apis/...`\n  - 验证: 所有共享类型的 DeepCopy 方法已生成\n\n- [ ] **T10** 验证共享类型编译正确\n  - 命令: `go build ./pkg/apis/...`\n  - 验证: 无编译错误\n\n- [ ] **T11** 运行 linter 检查\n  - 命令: `go vet ./pkg/apis/...`\n  - 验证: 无 lint 错误\n\n- [ ] **T12** 编写共享类型单元测试\n  - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n  - 验证: `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` 通过\n\n---\n\n## 依赖关系\n\n```\nT1 ─┬─> T6 ─> T9 ─> T10 ─> T11 ─> T12\nT2 ─┤\nT3 ─┤\nT4 ─┤\nT5 ─┘\nT7 ─> T9\nT8 ─> T9\n```\n\n**并行:** T2, T3, T4, T5 可并行执行\n\n## 验收标准\n\n- [ ] TargetPort, PodTemplateSpec, PodSpec, ContainerSpec 共享类型已定义\n- [ ] AuthMode 类型及常量已定义\n- [ ] 所有类型包含正确的 kubebuilder 验证标记\n- [ ] DeepCopy 方法已生成并编译正确\n- [ ] `go build ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n- [ ] `go vet ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n- [ ] 单元测试通过\n\n---\n\n# AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed (design in `pkg/workloadmanager/design.md`)\n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **T-001** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go` with GCConfig struct (Interval, BatchSize, MaxConcurrentDeletes, GracePeriod, EnableMetrics)\n- [ ] **T-002** Implement DefaultGCConfig() function with sensible defaults (5m interval, 50 batch, 10 concurrent, 30s grace)\n- [ ] **T-003** Create GCWorker struct with client, k8sClient, config, stopCh, cleanupMgr, expirationChecker fields\n- [ ] **T-004** Implement GCResult struct (ScannedCount, ExpiredCount, DeletedCount, FailedCount, Duration, Errors)\n- [ ] **T-005** Implement GCStats struct (TotalCycles, TotalDeleted, TotalFailed, LastRunTime, LastResult)\n\n### Phase 2: GC Worker Core\n\n- [ ] **T-006** Implement NewGCWorker() constructor function\n- [ ] **T-007** Implement GCWorker.Start(ctx) with ticker-based scheduling\n- [ ] **T-008** Implement GCWorker.Stop() method\n- [ ] **T-009** Implement GCWorker.runGCCycle() - main GC cycle logic\n- [ ] **T-010** Implement GCWorker.getNamespaces() to list target namespaces\n- [ ] **T-011** Implement GCWorker.processNamespace() to scan and delete expired resources in a namespace\n\n### Phase 3: Expiration Detection & Deletion\n\n- [ ] **T-012** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*AgentRuntime) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-013** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*CodeInterpreter) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-014** Implement GCWorker.getLastActivityTime() to extract from annotations\n- [ ] **T-015** Implement GCWorker.deleteAgentRuntime() with CleanupManager integration\n- [ ] **T-016** Implement GCWorker.deleteCodeInterpreter() with CleanupManager integration\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP API Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-017** Implement GCServer wrapper struct\n- [ ] **T-018** Implement GCTriggerResponse, GCStatusResponse, GCConfigUpdateRequest types\n- [ ] **T-019** Implement NewGCServer() constructor\n- [ ] **T-020** Implement GCServer.RegisterRoutes() with /gc/* endpoints\n- [ ] **T-021** Implement handleTrigger() - POST /api/v1/gc/trigger\n- [ ] **T-022** Implement handleStatus() - GET /api/v1/gc/status\n- [ ] **T-023** Implement handleConfigUpdate() - PUT /api/v1/gc/config\n\n### Phase 5: Configuration & Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-024** Add GCConfig to server Config struct\n- [ ] **T-025** Load GC config from environment variables (GC_INTERVAL, GC_BATCH_SIZE, GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES, GC_GRACE_PERIOD, GC_ENABLED)\n- [ ] **T-026** Initialize and start GC worker in server startup\n- [ ] **T-027** Register GC routes in server router setup\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n\n- [ ] **T-028** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go`\n- [ ] **T-029** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerIsExpired_* (with DeletionTimestamp, TTL, idle timeout)\n- [ ] **T-030** Write unit test: TestGCConfig validation\n- [ ] **T-031** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces\n- [ ] **T-032** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerStartStop\n- [ ] **T-033** Write unit test: TestGCServerRoutes\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T-034** Add error variables (ErrGCWorkerNotRunning, ErrGCAlreadyRunning, ErrInvalidConfig)\n- [ ] **T-035** Add logging at appropriate levels (V(4) cycle, V(2) failures, V(1) config)\n- [ ] **T-036** Verify code compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] **T-037** Run tests: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n- [ ] **T-038** Verify 80% test coverage for gc.go","additions":174,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775871669364,"end":1775871669416}}}}
